cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques in text generation systems, specifically in the context of incorporating external knowledge to improve the quality of generated text. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of selecting appropriate knowledge from large-scale knowledge bases (cs.IR - Information Retrieval) and integrating knowledge into the generation process (cs.NE - Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
